The family of the Kaduna State Governor, Nasir El-Rufai, are in a joyous mood as the governor’s son, Bashir, has given birth to a set of twins. Taking to his verified Twitter account on Sunday, Bashir revealed that his wife was delivered of identical twin boys. Stating that both his wife and children are in good condition, the ecstatic father tweeted, “Alhamdulillah. My wife just gave birth to beautiful identical twin boys. Mother is doing great. Father is ecstatic. Thank you, Allah. It was all you.” El-Rufai wedded Halima Kazaure, daughter of a former senator from Jigawa State, Ibrahim Kazaure, on November 21, 2020, in Abuja. The wedding was attended by Senate President, Ahmad Lawan; former emir of Kano, Muhammadu Sanusi II; Jigawa State Governor, Badaru Abubakar; Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni; and many other dignitaries. Stating that both his wife and children are in good condition, the ecstatic father tweeted, “Alhamdulillah. My wife just gave birth to beautiful identical twin boys. Mother is doing great. Father is ecstatic. Thank you, Allah. It was all you.”